File Photo: Xinhua China's Heilongjiang Province reported a new confirmed case of COVID-19 in Dongning on Thursday. The patient is a 40-year-old company employee. Dongning, located in the southeast of Heilongjiang Province, is adjacent to the Russian Far East. According to the Dongning official WeChat account, the patient, surnamed Kong, first tested positive at the Dongning Customs. He then received a second nucleic acid test at the Mudanjiang Center for Disease Control and Prevention, and the result was still positive. After expert consultation and comprehensive examination, the patient was diagnosed as a confirmed case with mild symptoms.Cities in Heilongjiang including Mudanjiang and Dongning immediately launched level-III emergency response, organized professional teams for flow regulation, detection and disinfection, and comprehensively carried out epidemiological investigation, nucleic acid testing, environmental disinfection and on-site control measures. Currently, after strict screening and tracing, all his close contacts have been quarantined and given nucleic acid tests. Personnel blockades and environmental nucleic acid tests have been implemented in the areas and places where the patient lives and frequents.In the next stage, Dongning will continue to carry out epidemiological investigation in traceability of the relevant personnel as well as nucleic acid testing, and strictly implement territorial prevention and control measures.Global Times 
